transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I'm on your website trying to figure out how to cancel a subscription.

Speaker 2: How do I cancel my subscription?

Speaker 1: We do not have any subscriptions.

Speaker 2: Give me your zip code.

Speaker 1: I have an automatic delivery.

Speaker 2: There's an automatic delivery that I'm being billed for each month and I want to stop it.

Speaker 1: And I don't see any way to stop it.

Speaker 2: Do you want to give me your zip code?

Speaker 1: 32024.

Speaker 2: And what is your first and last name?

Speaker 1: Ken Callahan.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: And what's going on with the medication?

Speaker 2: Are you just getting it too fast?

Speaker 1: No, I just don't want it anymore and I don't see any way of stopping this.

Speaker 2: The last order that was placed was not on purpose.

Speaker 1: All I tried to do was change the prescription and when I changed it, it said it was ordered.

Speaker 2: I didn't mean to order it, didn't want to order it.

Speaker 1: I'm willing to pay for that and forget about it, but I don't want it to happen again.

Speaker 2: I want my account canceled.

Speaker 1: Okay, but you realize that wasn't our fault, sir.

Speaker 2: I don't understand.

Speaker 1: You said you made a mistake there.

Speaker 2: No, I didn't make a mistake.

Speaker 1: All I did was went and changed the prescription.

Speaker 2: I was looking at what different prescriptions and I clicked the thing to change the prescription.

Speaker 1: I never entered and said order, yet it automatically popped me an email that said it was on order.

Speaker 2: Or it was waiting for a pharmacist and then the next thing you know it said it was ordered.

Speaker 1: I'm okay with that.

Speaker 2: I'm not bitching about getting that order.

Speaker 1: I just want it to never happen again.

Speaker 2: I want my name out of the system.

Speaker 1: I don't want another order to ever happen.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I understand, sir, but we didn't send you that order.

Speaker 1: You placed it yourself.

Speaker 2: Do you get what I mean?

Speaker 1: We won't send you orders.

Speaker 2: You can order as needed.

Speaker 1: You don't have to get it when you're not ready.

Speaker 2: Yeah, it has in my account a set.

Speaker 1: Let me pull it up.

Speaker 2: It says auto shipment.

Speaker 1: I understand you can set that up as you can set that up whenever, however you want.

Speaker 2: That's totally up to you.

Speaker 1: You do not have to get it when you're not ready.

Speaker 2: You can adjust that.

Speaker 1: You're missing my point.

Speaker 2: I'm in it right now.

Speaker 1: I just clicked the auto shipment, changed the frequency, and it says update next purchase.

Speaker 2: It does not give a choice to stop it.

Speaker 1: It's saying I'm going to get a 90-day supply.

Speaker 2: This is what I looked at last time when it automatically sent me an order.

Speaker 1: I changed the prescription.

Speaker 2: You can order as needed, though.

Speaker 1: That's what I'm telling you currently.

Speaker 2: I'm saying you can order this when you want to get your orders.

Speaker 1: Or you can adjust that to get them when you want them, the day, the month, every two months, every five months.

Speaker 2: Or you can just order as needed.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: If what you're saying is true, explain to me how I do it because I'm in the website right now.

Speaker 1: I'm looking.

Speaker 2: Only three things on this page are products, day supply, and bundles.

Speaker 1: I do it for you.

Speaker 2: Any kind of major changes to the medication has to be done with the pharmacy,

Speaker 1: so we have to contact the pharmacy to do any kind of major changes to the prescription.

Speaker 2: That's why you can't do it on your own.

Speaker 1: You can delay it a month and stop it for a month and so forth,

Speaker 2: but any large changes to the prescription has to be done on our side because we have to contact the pharmacy.

Speaker 1: Well, I would like for you to do whatever it is you have to do to make this never come to my house again.

Speaker 2: I don't want to pay for another one, and it's got an auto shipment set up already.

Speaker 1: Sir, but that's because you didn't set it up to get it when you want it or to set it up as needed.

Speaker 2: We're on the same page with this.

Speaker 1: How do I stop it is what I'm asking you.

Speaker 2: You're stopped, sir.

Speaker 1: You won't receive this again.

Speaker 2: We're going to cancel your prescription, okay?

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: You too.
